<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 14 at 5:16AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...An area of moderate to heavy snow showers will affect
northeastern Huron...Erie... Medina and Lorain Counties Until 630 AM
EDT....
At 513 AM EDT, radar indicated a band of moderate to heavy snow
showers extending from near Vermilion to Grafton, or 10 miles
northwest of Medina, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Visibility dropping to one half mile...
One to two inches of quick snow accumulation...
Locations impacted include...
Lorain, Elyria, Medina, Western Vermilion, Vermilion, Brunswick,
North Ridgeville, Wadsworth, Amherst, Grafton, Rittman, Wellington,
Lodi, New London, Wakeman, Chippewa Lake, Avon, Broadview Heights,
Eaton and Oberlin.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
